Kent Mitchell wrote:

&gt;In the abstract it is pretty hard to know what implicit branches might
&gt;occur.  There is no code for this at the source or bytecode level so you
&gt;just kind of &quot;have to know&quot; or have some other way to find the implicit
&gt;items.
&gt;  
&gt;
  Well, since all coverage tools based on the instrumentation it is 
quite easy to create explicit trap for these errors. In a worst case we 
can assume that any method could throw a runtime exception as well as 
certain language constructs such as a[n] or a.foo() (accordingly AIOOBE 
and NPE).
  This can be slightly optimized with some cached info about possible 
method exceptions created from simple inter-method DFA.

&gt;And I agree in this simple case that it&#39;s probably true you would want
&gt;it to pop out of here NumericFormatException but in the abstract it&#39;s
&gt;important for people to know the exception could occur when testing and
&gt;decide a) they want it to fly out or b) they don&#39;t and want to do
&gt;something else.  But more than enough said on this topic...
&gt;  
&gt;
  Right. :-)

  Eugene

